args:
As Luca works to evacuate the villagers,
Mascula appears seeking aid for an injured
imperial soldier. While Luca sympathizes with
his feelings, it only hardens his resolve to
keep fighting until the day is won.
We're old, and our days are few.\nLeave us. Save the children instead.

Guys, the imperial army is miiiles
behind us. We've got time to save
everybody, so there's no need to start
sacrificing your lives at this point.
Trust me. If there was a bad guy within\nten miles of this place, these sylvan\nears of mine would know about it.
(I doubted {player_name}'s\ncrazy plan at first, but I gotta admit,\nit's workin'!)
Shut the front door! You want us all to\nsplit up and run away, like, SEPARATELY?!
I think that's our best option.
It seems Emile can issue commands\ndirectly to the androids, but he's the\nONLY one who can do so.
So they either move as one big unit\nor they have to stay put? Interestin'.

And that's why we're going to split into
two groups. If one of them serves as bait
for the android forces, it will allow the
second group to escape.
Right! Keep moving, everybody!\nAnd don't worry—we'll protect\nyou no matter what.
I feel guilty that we're making a sylvan\nlike yourself protect us.
I've heard the sylvan people have a\ndeep loathing for humans.
Hell, I've got boatloads of human friends—\nplus some other races besides!
I mean, who cares about doing things just\nbecause we happen to be human or sylvan\nor whatever? That's boring.
Hey, you're that android from before!\nEr, and help you with what, exactly?
There are many humans over there\nwho are injured and unable to move.
I want to treat them but...I'm an android.\nI don't know enough about organic bodies.\nPlease...
Hey, look, I'd love to help you out,\nbut I'm already trying to evacuate\nall these folks, so...
Please don't worry about us. If there are\nothers who need your assistance,\nby all means go to them now.
I don't wish to sound unappreciative of\nyour efforts, but if you have the chance\nto help others, you should do so.
Well, when you put it like that...\nOkay, android. Show me where all\nthese wounded folks are hiding.
Thank you very much.\nAlso, you may call me Mascula.
I'm Luca. Nice to meet ya...I think?\nI'm still feelin' you out, so we'll\nsave the handshake for later.
Mascula, these are imperial soldiers!\nAre THEY the injured people you're\ntrying to help?!
Yes, that's right.\nIs there a problem?
Well, hell! I thought you were on our side,\nbut I guess I was wrong!
You're clearly still workin' for the Empire\nif you want us to heal their wounded!
No, that's not it.\nI'm not ＂with＂ the Empire.
Then why do you want me to help 'em?!
Is it strange to help one who is injured?
I don't understand. Why is this bad?
Do your ＂sides＂ mean so much that you\nwould leave them to die?
I don't want to hurt anyone.\nI seek only to help, without exception.
Is that such a bad thing?
No, of course not...\nOh, dammit! Fine!

Look, I'll give 'em some of my sylvan
medicine, okay? That'll keep 'em from
bleedin' out or getting any kind of nasty
rotting diseases.
Sorry you had to go wasting the good\nstuff on a guy like me...
Yeah, well, you can thank this android\nfor tippin' my hand, I guess.
Heh. Same old Luca. You're from the\nvillage near Myriage Lake, yeah?
Wait, how do you know that?
My hometown's close to that village,\nso I know some of the folks there.
Didn't stop you from joining the\nimperial army though, did it?
Didn't have much choice in the matter.\nIf you're conscripted and refuse to serve,\nthe Empire punishes your family.
Ugh... Yeah, well, I guess even imperial\nsoldiers have their reasons.
Thank you for the medicine, Luca.\nYou are a good person.
Actually, I should be thanking you.
Remember all that stuff you told me\nabout life having value no matter whose\nside it might happen to be on?

Well, maybe I needed a little reminder.
Hell, I was just going on to some villager
about how race didn't matter, yet I turned
around and did the same damn thing.
You opened my eyes to that.\nSo...thanks.
I am glad that you understand.\nAnd as I said, you are a good person.
Yeah, maybe I am—but that doesn't \nmean I'm gonna stop fightin'.
Sometimes you gotta fight for what's\nimportant—even if it means hurtin'\nsomeone else.
I still believe there is a way to end\nconflicts without fighting.
Yeah, maybe there is—but while we\ntake the time to try and figure that out,\nmore people are gonna suffer.
That's why I'm gonna keep fightin'\nfor what matters.
And if you get in the way of that...\nWell, I'll do what I gotta do.
Hey, guys? Sorry to cut in, but I think\nyou better get out of here real soon.
We were left behind here since we were\ninjured and couldn't keep up with our\nforces.

The main imperial army won't be all that
far. You should hurry and get out of here.
I know it's weird for me to be telling you
this but... Well, there it is.
Yikes! Thanks for the heads-up, pal.\n...Come on, everyone. We're leaving.
I am to blame if the imperial army attacks.\nSo I must protect you.
I thought you didn't want to fight.

I do not—yet I can still be of assistance.
I can take their weapons away from them,
serve as a distraction to draw their eyes,
or any other number of things.
Man, you really are an oddball.\nStill, you seem okay for the most part,\nso if you wanna tag along, feel free.
I knew you were a good person.

Boy, you just say whatever pops into the
ol' melon, huh? I ain't really used to folks
who are that... I dunno. Genuine?
Or childlike, maybe.
Nah, it's fine. I mean, sure, it can be\nannoying sometimes, but like I said,\nyou seem pretty all right.
＂Pretty all right＂ is an expression of favor,\nyes? I like you too, Luca!
Ha ha! Sure, Mascula, whatever you say.\nRegardless, welcome aboard.
You there! Did you find them?!
Yes, sir. They appear to be massing in\nthe ruined village down the way.
Ha! They've been scuttling about in an\nattempt to escape, but we've cornered\nthem at last. Now, I will see this settled!
Chelle called this thing a trump card,\nso if I use it...
Yes! This time I will CRUSH THEM ALL!
